{"id":1925,"date":"2021-01-27T08:00:15","date_gmt":"2021-01-27T16:00:15","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/?p=1925"},"modified":"2021-08-18T04:33:32","modified_gmt":"2021-08-18T11:33:32","slug":"the-benefits-of-becoming-a-non-resident-importer-in-canada","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/blog\/the-benefits-of-becoming-a-non-resident-importer-in-canada\/","title":{"rendered":"The Benefits of Becoming a Non Resident Importer in Canada"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If your business is based in the US and you\u2019re interested in tapping into the Canadian market, becoming a Canadian Non-Resident Importer (NRI) might be your best option.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Non-Resident Importer Program is run by the Canadian Border Services Agency (CBSA), and its purpose is to enable international exporters to sell their products to Canadian customers without having a physical business presence in Canada.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are numerous benefits to becoming a Non Resident Importer as well as some risks to consider. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Is your import-export business just starting? Don\u2019t miss our <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/blog\/how-to-start-an-import-export-business\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">complete guide<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1923\" src=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/nana-smirnova-IEiAmhXehwE-unsplash-1024x653.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"383\" srcset=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/nana-smirnova-IEiAmhXehwE-unsplash-scaled.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/nana-smirnova-IEiAmhXehwE-unsplash-300x191.jpg 300w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/nana-smirnova-IEiAmhXehwE-unsplash-768x490.jpg 768w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/nana-smirnova-IEiAmhXehwE-unsplash-1536x980.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/nana-smirnova-IEiAmhXehwE-unsplash-2048x1307.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><b>Advantages of Becoming a Non-Resident Importer<\/b><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">US companies receive lots of benefits when they are both the exporter of record and the non-resident importer of record. These include:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Price certainty. <\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The US company can incorporate fees (such as customs clearance fees, taxes and duties, and transportation costs) into the sale price of the product so Canadian customers don\u2019t have to deal with unexpected costs.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Convenience for customers. <\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Canadian customers can buy the US company\u2019s products as easily as they can purchase domestic products.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reduced costs. <\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The US company can clear the consolidated shipment faster and save money on shipping costs.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Improved tracking. <\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The US company has total control over the shipment throughout the process and can track it easily, avoiding customs delays.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Competitive advantage. <\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The US company can expand its market reach into Canada while maintaining an edge over its competitors.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><i>Supply chain efficiency. <\/i>The US company is not required to have any warehouses, distribution centers, or stores in Canada and can build a supply chain that suits its business model.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1922\" src=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/pexels-pixabay-209224-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/pexels-pixabay-209224-scaled.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/pexels-pixabay-209224-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/pexels-pixabay-209224-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/pexels-pixabay-209224-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/pexels-pixabay-209224-2048x1365.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><b>Risks and Responsibilities<\/b><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It\u2019s important to be aware of the risks and responsibilities inherent in becoming a non-resident importer of record. They are as follows:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The non-resident importer of record is held responsible for the import declaration.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The non-resident importer of record must calculate and pay all taxes and duties.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The non-resident importer of record is expected to follow all participating government agency regulations.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As you can see, the non-resident importer needs to be familiar with customs documentation, import tax Canada, and all relevant rules and regulations.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Curious which products are illegal to ship internationally? Click <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/blog\/when-shipping-turns-illegal-things-you-are-not-allowed-to-ship\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><b>How to Become a Non-Resident Importer in Canada<\/b><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Are you ready to take the next step and become a non-resident importer in Canada? There are two main steps to this process.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First, you\u2019ll need to apply for a Business Number (BN) from the Canada Revenue Agency (CRA). You will be assigned a 15-digit number that will allow you to transact with government agencies.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next, you\u2019ll need to register an Agreement for Maintaining Books and Records Outside of Canada with the Canada Border Services Agency (CBSA) informing them of where your records will be kept. You\u2019ll need to write a letter of undertaking that states you will pay for a CBSA agent\u2019s travel expenses in the event of a company audit.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1921\" src=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cytonn-photography-GJao3ZTX9gU-unsplash-1024x684.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"401\" srcset=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cytonn-photography-GJao3ZTX9gU-unsplash-scaled.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cytonn-photography-GJao3ZTX9gU-unsplash-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cytonn-photography-GJao3ZTX9gU-unsplash-768x513.jpg 768w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cytonn-photography-GJao3ZTX9gU-unsplash-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/cytonn-photography-GJao3ZTX9gU-unsplash-2048x1367.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><b>Hiring a Customs Broker (Canada) to Establish Your Non-Resident Importer Account<\/b><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.trade.gov\/canada-non-resident-importer-program\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">International Trade Administration of Canada<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> recommends that you hire a customs broker to assist you with the non-resident importer process. But what is a customs broker exactly? Here are the ways a customs broker can support your company as you start exporting goods internationally to Canada:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The customs broker will ensure your company is fully compliant as an exporter to Canada.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The customs broker will inform you of any United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) benefits you are eligible for.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The customs broker will calculate the fees which influence the product\u2019s final price (such as duties, taxes, transportation costs, and brokerage fees).<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The customs broker will clarify Canadian taxes.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The customs broker will help compile the necessary documentation.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The customs broker will create the non-resident importer account by procuring a Canadian Business Number and developing the Agreement for Maintaining Books and Records Outside of Canada.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you want to hire the best customs broker Canada has to offer, look no further. At <\/span><\/i><b><i>BorderBuddy<\/i><\/b><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, our goal is to make the customs process cheaper, faster, and easier for you. We offer solutions for businesses of all sizes, so give us a <\/span><\/i><a href=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/contact\/\"><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">call<\/span><\/i><\/a><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> today.<\/span><\/i><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>If your business is based in the US and you\u2019re interested in tapping into the Canadian market, becoming a Canadian Non-Resident Importer (NRI) might be your best option.\u00a0 The Non-Resident Importer Program is run by the Canadian Border Services Agency (CBSA), and its purpose is to enable international exporters to sell their products to Canadian&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1924,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"inline_featured_image":false,"_genesis_hide_title":false,"_genesis_hide_breadcrumbs":false,"_genesis_hide_singular_image":false,"_genesis_hide_footer_widgets":false,"_genesis_custom_body_class":"","_genesis_custom_post_class":"","_genesis_layout":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[9],"tags":[],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v22.4 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>The Benefits of Becoming a Non Resident Importer in Canada &#187; Blog &#187; BorderBuddy<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"If your business is based in the US and you\u2019re interested in tapping into the Canadian market, becoming a Canadian Non-Resident Importer (NRI) might be\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"